    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-05-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-05-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="159" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d159">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 159.</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Scruggs</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-05-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 16,
                            1885</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 36.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                        182, of December 26 last, touching the abuses of American citizenship, and
                        in which you cite the case of Aurelio F. Pinzon, a native and resident of
                        Colombia, who claims to be a naturalized citizen of the United States, and
                        as such has appealed to you for protection.</p>
                <p>On Mr. Pinzon’s own statement the Government of the United States is under no
                        obligation to protect him as against the country of his original allegiance,
                        his certificate of naturalization having been admittedly obtained in fraud
                        of the United States statutes.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>T. F. BAYARD.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
